// this exercise is to demonstrate the use of the MSC Debugger
// and the construction of a Memory Map!
// YOU USE THE DEBUGGER FOR 2 JOBS: 
//    (1) EXAMINE THE STATE(VALUE) OF VARIABLES AND EXPRESSIONS!
//    (2) Trace the flow of control, or the flow of EXECUTION

// Step 1: Let's write a simple program!
//
// Step 2: Use the Debugger: We ALWAYS begin by putting in BREAK POINTS: A break is a line of code at which
//         the debugger will PAUSE and then you can:  Examine the values of variables, and expressions!

var a,b,c;
let x,y,z;

a =1;
a++;
b =2;
b--;
c =3;

for (  ; a>b++ ;  ){
    
}
